    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ariadne-entry\"><p><strong>Source:</strong> Ariadne's Book of Legends - Alpha v1.2, p. 76-77.</p><p>Legendary Blast</p><p>Prerequisite: Level 20+ Warlock, a Warlock Cantrip That Deals Damage</p><p>Choose a warlock cantrip that deals damage with a casting time of 1 action. When you cast that cantrip, you can expend 1 Legendary Point to perform a Legendary Blast instead. When you do so, you make only one spell attack with a range of 120 feet. On a hit, you deal 4d10 x 5 force damage. On a critical hit, you do not multiply the damage by 2, but instead deal 6d10 x 5 force damage.</p><p>When you hit with this special attack, you inflict any additional effects normally applied by your cantrip. If you possess Eldritch Invocations that modify your cantrip’s range, they also modify your Legendary Blast. Legendary Blast counts as a higher-tier effect for the purposes of Tiers of Magic.</p><p>In addition, when you cast your chosen cantrip, you ignore any Limited Magic Immunity that would render a creature immune to cantrip-level spells.</p><p>Repeatable. You can gain this invocation more than once. Each time you do so, choose a different eligible cantrip.</p></div>",
